33
00:04:45,919 --> 00:04:48,287
<i>It's Jumping Jack Flash</i>
<i>increasing his advantage.</i>

34
00:04:48,288 --> 00:04:50,389
<i>Hello There, Stranger</i>
<i>making a run now.</i>

35
00:04:53,893 --> 00:04:55,661
<i>Entering the far turn.</i>

36
00:04:55,662 --> 00:04:57,029
<i>It's Jumping Jack Flash.</i>

37
00:04:57,030 --> 00:04:59,798
[Crowd shouting]

38
00:04:59,799 --> 00:05:01,734
<i>Holding on through</i>
<i>this free-for-all from home.</i>

39
00:05:01,735 --> 00:05:03,402
<i>And it's Jumping Jack Flash</i>

40
00:05:03,403 --> 00:05:05,637
<i>leaving this field</i>
<i>in his wake.</i>

41
00:05:05,638 --> 00:05:08,207
<i>A furlong and a half up,</i>
<i>Jumping Jack Flash</i>

42
00:05:08,208 --> 00:05:11,110
<i>by seven...</i>
<i>incredible, ten lengths now.</i>

43
00:05:11,111 --> 00:05:12,244
<i>They're coming to the wire.</i>

44
00:05:12,245 --> 00:05:13,245
<i>Jumping Jack Flash.</i>

45
00:05:13,246 --> 00:05:14,747
Jack, that's one hell
of a horse.

46
00:05:14,748 --> 00:05:16,582
See you
at the breeder's cup.
Thanks, Andy.

47
00:05:16,583 --> 00:05:18,650
<i>[Man on TV]</i>
<i>He was much faster,</i>
<i>and he blew them away.</i>

48
00:05:18,651 --> 00:05:19,918
<i>He won it</i>
<i>by 10 1/2 lengths.</i>

49
00:05:19,919 --> 00:05:23,956
You bet against
your own horse?

50
00:05:23,957 --> 00:05:25,924
I bet against
my father's horse.

51
00:05:25,925 --> 00:05:28,560
Now, why'd
you do that?

52
00:05:28,561 --> 00:05:32,364
'Cause nobody else does.

53
00:05:32,365 --> 00:05:35,367
[Bluesy guitar music]

54
00:05:35,368 --> 00:05:39,471
# #

55
00:05:39,472 --> 00:05:41,206
What did you think
of that chestnut mare, Jack?

56
00:05:41,207 --> 00:05:42,341
That Jimmy Buck's
a good stud.

57
00:05:42,342 --> 00:05:43,809
I think she's gonna throw
us a winner.

58
00:05:43,810 --> 00:05:45,277
Not just Woodbine,

59
00:05:45,278 --> 00:05:47,413
Louisville, Kentucky,
Baltimore, Maryland,

60
00:05:47,414 --> 00:05:48,480
the Big Apple.

61
00:05:48,481 --> 00:05:49,515
What do you think?

62
00:05:49,516 --> 00:05:50,849
I think I got too much
to do

63
00:05:50,850 --> 00:05:52,651
to worry about races
that haven't been run,

64
00:05:52,652 --> 00:05:54,119
by horses
that haven't been born.

65
00:05:54,120 --> 00:05:57,489
Yeah, don't plan your future
around my horses, Sonny.

66
00:05:57,490 --> 00:05:58,624
I got plans of my own.

67
00:05:58,625 --> 00:05:59,892
I may surprise you yet, Dad.

68
00:05:59,893 --> 00:06:01,193
<i>[Horse neighs]</i>

69
00:06:01,194 --> 00:06:02,461
See you
in New York, Jack.

70
00:06:02,462 --> 00:06:04,296
Can't figure you missing
Saturday's race.

71
00:06:04,297 --> 00:06:05,731
Yeah, you know,

72
00:06:05,732 --> 00:06:08,133
<i>she's got some big shindig</i>
<i>down in the islands.</i>

73
00:06:08,134 --> 00:06:09,234
Wouldn't want
to miss that.

74
00:06:09,235 --> 00:06:11,603
Hey, you all set?

75
00:06:11,604 --> 00:06:13,472
All set.

76
00:06:13,473 --> 00:06:14,740
Careful, Sonny.

77
00:06:14,741 --> 00:06:17,409
<i>You don't want</i>
<i>to spoil your breakfast.</i>

78
00:06:17,410 --> 00:06:18,410
[Dog barking]

79
00:06:18,411 --> 00:06:19,411
<i>(Paulie)</i>
<i>Hey, biscuit.</i>

80
00:06:19,412 --> 00:06:20,446
<i>(Gena)</i>
<i>Biscuit!</i>

81
00:06:20,447 --> 00:06:21,613
<i>Hey, don't scare her.</i>

82
00:06:21,614 --> 00:06:22,748
<i>Earl,</i>
<i>can you get the dog?</i>

83
00:06:22,749 --> 00:06:23,749
What a good dog.

84
00:06:23,750 --> 00:06:25,250
What are you up to, huh?

85
00:06:25,251 --> 00:06:26,719
Yeah, thanks, Paulie.

86
00:06:26,720 --> 00:06:28,687
You guys heading out now,
Uncle Earl?

87
00:06:28,688 --> 00:06:29,955
Yeah, we are.

88
00:06:29,956 --> 00:06:31,523
Listen, I'm not gonna
be here Saturday.

89
00:06:31,524 --> 00:06:34,526
I want you
to look after my horse, okay?

90
00:06:34,527 --> 00:06:36,161
Don't you worry
about Flash.

91
00:06:36,162 --> 00:06:37,596
You just...

92
00:06:37,597 --> 00:06:38,897
you have
a good time.

93
00:06:38,898 --> 00:06:43,502
Run along there,
biscuit.

94
00:06:46,406 --> 00:06:47,506
There you go.

95
00:06:47,507 --> 00:06:49,141
<i>(Gena)</i>
<i>Oh, thank you.</i>

96
00:06:49,142 --> 00:06:52,011
(Earl)
All right.

97
00:06:54,414 --> 00:06:57,016
[Engine revs]

98
00:07:09,763 --> 00:07:12,264
Where you been?

99
00:07:12,265 --> 00:07:14,633
Jesus Christ.

100
00:07:14,634 --> 00:07:16,001
I stopped for lunch,
Jackson.

101
00:07:16,002 --> 00:07:17,236
Liquid lunch?

102
00:07:17,237 --> 00:07:19,371
I want you
to get that roan,

103
00:07:19,372 --> 00:07:21,240
get her up to the dd
in London.

104
00:07:21,241 --> 00:07:23,509
Get her bred
to rambling river.

105
00:07:23,510 --> 00:07:24,510
Rambling river?

106
00:07:24,511 --> 00:07:25,577
Why that stud?

107
00:07:25,578 --> 00:07:27,446
Dean, you show up late,
half in the bag.

108
00:07:27,447 --> 00:07:28,947
You want
to ask questions?

109
00:07:28,948 --> 00:07:30,149
Show up Early sometime.

110
00:07:30,150 --> 00:07:31,617
We'll talk about
the business.

111
00:07:31,618 --> 00:07:33,952
<i>And these two clowns are gonna</i>
<i>run the stables?</i>

112
00:07:33,953 --> 00:07:36,021
No, and neither are you,
Sonny.

113
00:07:36,022 --> 00:07:37,623
Now go on.

114
00:07:37,624 --> 00:07:38,791
Get that mare loaded.

115
00:07:38,792 --> 00:07:39,958
Get her up to London.

116
00:07:39,959 --> 00:07:41,660
I'm going
to woodbine.

117
00:07:41,661 --> 00:07:47,132
Sonny, you can carry on
with your duties there.

118
00:07:47,133 --> 00:07:50,069
[Doors slam, engine revs]

119
00:07:56,343 --> 00:07:59,044
[Softly]
Pooh.

120
00:08:07,287 --> 00:08:09,088
When you runnin' him?

121
00:08:09,089 --> 00:08:11,156
Claimer, Saturday,
Fort Erie.

122
00:08:11,157 --> 00:08:12,958
What's he done?

123
00:08:12,959 --> 00:08:15,194
Well, he won last month.

124
00:08:15,195 --> 00:08:16,395
<i>[Horse neighs]</i>

125
00:08:16,396 --> 00:08:18,497
<i>Come out of it</i>
<i>with a cracked hoof, though.</i>

126
00:08:18,498 --> 00:08:22,234
I epoxied it.

127
00:08:22,235 --> 00:08:23,902
Looks all right now,

128
00:08:23,903 --> 00:08:25,671
<i>but I won't know for sure</i>
<i>till I run him again.</i>

129
00:08:25,672 --> 00:08:27,206
Are you racing those mares?

130
00:08:27,207 --> 00:08:28,407
No, they're
finished racing.

131
00:08:28,408 --> 00:08:30,576
That chestnut's
in foal.

132
00:08:30,577 --> 00:08:33,479
How the hell
you making a living, Pete?

133
00:08:33,480 --> 00:08:36,548
Who said I was?

134
00:08:36,549 --> 00:08:39,118
I got my corn
to come off.

135
00:08:39,119 --> 00:08:40,586
Could be I get another couple
of wins

136
00:08:40,587 --> 00:08:41,954
out of this gelding.

137
00:08:41,955 --> 00:08:43,789
Could be he'll break down again
next time out.

138
00:08:43,790 --> 00:08:44,890
That's not a young horse.

139
00:08:44,891 --> 00:08:46,558
You're a pessimistic
son of a bitch

140
00:08:46,559 --> 00:08:50,596
<i>for someone who just got out</i>
<i>of jail.</i>

141
00:09:01,641 --> 00:09:04,677
<i>(Sonny)</i>
<i>Build a subdivision right</i>
<i>at the base of the escarpment.</i>

142
00:09:04,678 --> 00:09:06,345
<i>You know, estate lots,</i>

143
00:09:06,346 --> 00:09:08,647
<i>every house overlooking</i>
<i>the golf course.</i>

144
00:09:08,648 --> 00:09:09,982
<i>You just bulldoze</i>
<i>that farmhouse</i>

145
00:09:09,983 --> 00:09:11,150
<i>and those shacks.</i>

146
00:09:11,151 --> 00:09:13,118
<i>You build a clubhouse</i>
<i>right there.</i>

147
00:09:15,121 --> 00:09:17,556
Beautiful.

148
00:09:17,557 --> 00:09:20,025
You think you can swing
all this?

149
00:09:20,026 --> 00:09:21,927
You know we're talking about
a lot of money here.

150
00:09:21,928 --> 00:09:26,131
I can't believe
you'd ask me that, rock.

151
00:09:29,269 --> 00:09:33,539
Hey.

152
00:09:33,540 --> 00:09:35,708
Well, if it isn't
the prodigal.

153
00:09:35,709 --> 00:09:36,709
[Laughs]

154
00:09:36,710 --> 00:09:37,843
And me
with no calf to kill.

155
00:09:37,844 --> 00:09:39,244
<i>Hey, how's that bible</i>
<i>of yours feel</i>

156
00:09:39,245 --> 00:09:41,146
about serving a man
a rye whiskey?

157
00:09:46,986 --> 00:09:50,055
Hey, Bonnie,
Dan Rockwell been in?

158
00:09:50,056 --> 00:09:51,657
I've not seen
his royal highness today.

159
00:09:51,658 --> 00:09:55,527
I'll have a 50, Bonnie,
and get Ray here another.

160
00:09:55,528 --> 00:09:56,628
How you doing, buddy?

161
00:09:56,629 --> 00:09:58,130
Never better.

162
00:09:58,131 --> 00:09:59,231
I thought you were out

163
00:09:59,232 --> 00:10:00,432
at the tar sands
getting rich.

164
00:10:00,433 --> 00:10:02,568
I've been back
over a year.

165
00:10:02,569 --> 00:10:03,902
You back farming?

166
00:10:03,903 --> 00:10:05,571
Yeah, I was.

167
00:10:05,572 --> 00:10:07,172
I'm a roofer these days.

168
00:10:07,173 --> 00:10:11,310
Old man sold the farm,
sold it to Sonny Stanton.

169
00:10:11,311 --> 00:10:14,313
Looks like Sonny wants to buy up
the whole concession.

170
00:10:14,314 --> 00:10:15,514
Why the hell
would he do that?

171
00:10:15,515 --> 00:10:16,515
He's no farmer.

172
00:10:16,516 --> 00:10:17,516
Yeah, no shit.

173
00:10:17,517 --> 00:10:19,118
What about you?

174
00:10:19,119 --> 00:10:20,652
Still playing ball
down in the states?

175
00:10:20,653 --> 00:10:24,823
No, I've been out of it
a couple years.

176
00:10:24,824 --> 00:10:25,924
<i>Looking for a job</i>
<i>right now.</i>

177
00:10:25,925 --> 00:10:27,226
<i>Really?</i>
<i>Well, I'm shorthanded,</i>

178
00:10:27,227 --> 00:10:28,427
<i>busy as hell.</i>

179
00:10:28,428 --> 00:10:30,029
<i>I'm here to pick up</i>
<i>another subdivision.</i>

180
00:10:30,030 --> 00:10:31,797
You want to lay shingles

181
00:10:31,798 --> 00:10:33,365
for a living?

182
00:10:33,366 --> 00:10:35,334
You can start tomorrow
if you want.

183
00:10:35,335 --> 00:10:36,402
All right.

184
00:10:36,403 --> 00:10:39,338
Great.

185
00:10:39,339 --> 00:10:40,706
I got to hit the gents'.

186
00:10:46,112 --> 00:10:47,212
How you doing, Steve?

187
00:10:58,391 --> 00:10:59,458
What are you doing
here?

188
00:10:59,459 --> 00:11:01,627
Shit.

189
00:11:01,628 --> 00:11:03,562
Taking a leak.

190
00:11:03,563 --> 00:11:05,097
Hope I'm better at it
than you.

191
00:11:05,098 --> 00:11:06,398
Psycho.

192
00:11:06,399 --> 00:11:09,668
Put in 44 units
in this cul-de-sac right here.

193
00:11:09,669 --> 00:11:11,370
Got to be finished
in a month,

194
00:11:11,371 --> 00:11:13,038
not two months, okay?

195
00:11:13,039 --> 00:11:16,642
Sonny and I got
a pretty big job coming up.

196
00:11:16,643 --> 00:11:17,843
Could be good for you,
Steve.

197
00:11:17,844 --> 00:11:19,044
It'll be done.

198
00:11:19,045 --> 00:11:20,145
Good.

199
00:11:20,146 --> 00:11:21,180
This is Ray.

200
00:11:21,181 --> 00:11:23,182
He's working for me.

201
00:11:23,183 --> 00:11:24,183
All right.

202
00:11:24,184 --> 00:11:25,250
That's Ray Dokes.

203
00:11:29,356 --> 00:11:31,090
This asshole ain't working
on my site.

204
00:11:31,091 --> 00:11:32,691
You're not the only
developer out there.

205
00:11:32,692 --> 00:11:33,926
You can shove
your subdivision

206
00:11:33,927 --> 00:11:34,760
up your ass.

207
00:11:37,097 --> 00:11:38,731
Asshole.

208
00:11:38,732 --> 00:11:40,265
Hey, hey, hey,
I got nothing against ex-cons.

209
00:11:42,102 --> 00:11:44,436
I just don't
trust them.

210
00:11:44,437 --> 00:11:45,270
Fuck you.

211
00:11:58,385 --> 00:12:02,688
Heh, first free drink I've had
in a while.

212
00:12:02,689 --> 00:12:04,289
I'll see you
in the morning.

213
00:12:07,761 --> 00:12:10,329
[Birds chirping]

214
00:12:25,378 --> 00:12:29,114
[Hammering and saw noises]

215
00:12:29,115 --> 00:12:31,850
[Gunshot]

216
00:12:46,132 --> 00:12:46,865
What are you shooting?

217
00:12:49,002 --> 00:12:53,372
Rats.

218
00:13:03,283 --> 00:13:04,283
You got to stay out here.

219
00:13:04,284 --> 00:13:06,218
Homer's inside.

220
00:13:06,219 --> 00:13:08,454
You'll remember,
he's not your biggest fan.

221
00:13:08,455 --> 00:13:12,257
How is homer, anyway?

222
00:13:12,258 --> 00:13:14,159
He's fine.

223
00:13:14,160 --> 00:13:15,828
He's 75.

224
00:13:15,829 --> 00:13:17,396
He's bound to slow down
a little.

225
00:13:22,936 --> 00:13:24,870
This place has gone to hell
in a handbasket.

226
00:13:24,871 --> 00:13:28,340
You know more about that
particular destination than me.

227
00:13:28,341 --> 00:13:31,443
Besides, Sonny Stanton didn't
share your point of view.

228
00:13:31,444 --> 00:13:33,112
He's been trying
to buy the place.

229
00:13:33,113 --> 00:13:35,848
Is homer gonna sell?

230
00:13:35,849 --> 00:13:37,149
Not if I have
any say in it.

231
00:13:37,150 --> 00:13:39,885
Sonny's not used
to hearing the word "no."

232
00:13:39,886 --> 00:13:42,354
Well, he's gonna hear it
from me.

233
00:13:42,355 --> 00:13:44,890
That's Pete Culpepper's
truck.

234
00:13:44,891 --> 00:13:46,792
You sure you should be
driving

235
00:13:46,793 --> 00:13:49,661
if I can smell the whiskey
from here?

236
00:13:49,662 --> 00:13:56,035
Oh, I can make it
another mile or two.

237
00:13:56,036 --> 00:13:57,436
Why, you worried
about me?

238
00:13:58,805 --> 00:14:00,406
Not anymore, I'm not.

239
00:14:07,147 --> 00:14:10,149
[Easy guitar music]

240
00:14:10,150 --> 00:14:18,457
# #

241
00:14:34,841 --> 00:14:35,941
so how's Etta?

242
00:14:38,411 --> 00:14:39,478
How do you know
I saw Etta?

243
00:14:41,548 --> 00:14:44,116
